00:14:08.554 --> 00:14:10.454
recent fiscal report about how we're going to

245
00:14:11.434 --> 00:14:13.774
pay for superannuation and so on

246
00:14:14.754 --> 00:14:18.724
with a smaller tax base as the workforce shrinks, I think treating this

247
00:14:18.774 --> 00:14:22.574
whole thing as a systems challenge is going to be the biggest thing that we can do

248
00:14:22.614 --> 00:14:23.494
to get this right.

249
00:14:24.814 --> 00:14:27.934
We're still going to need to be building more aged care facilities.

250
00:14:27.954 --> 00:14:29.834
We're still going to need to build more hospital care.

251
00:14:29.873 --> 00:14:32.954
There is not a world, I think, in which we don't still have to do that.

252
00:14:32.964 --> 00:14:36.734
But we can reduce the amount at which we have to do that by thinking about those

253
00:14:37.894 --> 00:14:41.454
home care supports and other public health interventions that can keep people

254
00:14:41.494 --> 00:14:43.514
healthier for longer and keep them out of hospital. Yeah.

255
00:14:44.154 --> 00:14:46.454
So which brings us to health. Next slide, please.

256
00:14:48.214 --> 00:14:49.174
What time is it? Okay, cool.

